<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Piteous" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Piteous,</orth> 1) compassionate: <cit><quote>these eyes, but for thy p. lips, no more had seen,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 504" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 504</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a wretched image, that p. looks to Phrygian shepherds lent,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1502" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1502</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>tell your p. heart,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 14</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>in thy p. heart plant thou thine ear,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 5.3.126" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 3, 126</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) exciting compassion: <cit><quote>he pens her p. clamours in her head,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 681" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 681</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>p. plainings of the pretty babes,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.73" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 73</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.1.40" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 1, 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 3.3.91" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 3, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.163" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 163</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.5.73" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.2.158" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 2, 158</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.3.2" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 1.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 3.2.54" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 54</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.3.86" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.180" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 180</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.202" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 2, 202</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.1.82" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 1, 82</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.1.82" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 1, 82</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.4.128" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 128</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.214" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 214</bibl>.
<lb />3) miserable, wretched, pitiful: <cit><quote>in an act of this importance 'twere most p. to be wild,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 2.1.182" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 1, 182</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>or p. they will look, like drowned mice,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.2.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 2, 12</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his p. and unpitied end,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.74" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 74</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>